Class CommandInterpreter

java.lang.Object
org.example.galaxy_trucker.Commands.CommandInterpreter
public class CommandInterpreter extends Object
The CommandInterpreter class is responsible for parsing and interpreting command strings, converting them into appropriate Command objects for execution. The commands are used in the context of a multiplayer game system.

      public Command interpret(String commandString)
      Interprets a given command string, identifying the corresponding command creator and using it to construct and return a Command object.
      Parameters:
      commandString - the string representation of the command to interpret
      Returns:
      an instance of Command created based on the given command string
      Throws:
      IllegalArgumentException - if the command is not recognized
